Bren school home / About


Facts and figures

BREN SCHOOL FACTS

Only computing-focused school in UC system
Founded in 1968 as Department of Information and Computer Science
Established in 2002 as an independent school, the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences (ICS)

RANKINGS

US News & World Report (2022)#14 Computer Science graduate program and #12 Computer Science undergraduate program among public universities #7 Software Engineering undergraduate program#18 Statistics graduate program among public universities
Microsoft Academic Search website ranking of authors and organizations by citations (as of March 11, 2014)UC Irvine 20th among U.S. universities in computer science. Some top subareas:- Human-computer interaction: 4th- Software engineering: 9th- Databases: 8th

BY THE NUMBERS  – Download PDF


3,900+ students
100+ Faculty (full-time and lecturers)
70+ Staff
15,000+ Alumni
Three departments: Computer Science, Informatics, Statistics

UNDERGRADUATE PROGRAMS
3,100+ undergraduate students in seven majors

Computer Science
Data Science
Informatics
Software Engineering 
Game Design and Interactive Media 
Business Information Management (joint with the Paul Merage School of Business)
Computer Science & Engineering (joint with the Henry Samueli School of Engineering)

GRADUATE PROGRAMS
530+ graduate students

Computer Science (M.S., Ph.D.)
Informatics: (M.S., Ph.D.)
Software Engineering: (M.S., Ph.D.)
Statistics: (M.S., Ph.D.)
Networked Systems: (M.S., Ph.D.)

Professional Master Programs
350+ professional master's students

Master of Computer Science
Master of Data Science 
Master of Embedded and Cyber-Physical Systems
Master of Human-Computer Interaction and Design
Master of Software Engineering


INFLUENTIAL FACULTY AND ALUMNI
Our faculty

2 members of the National Academy of Engineering: Michael Carey (2012), Judy Olson (2018)
10 Fellows of the American Association for the Advancement of Science (AAAS): Pierre Baldi, Geoffrey Bowker, Rina Dechter, Paul Dourish, David Eppstein, Michael Franz, Michael Goodrich, Ramesh Jain, Eric Mjolsness, Annie Qu, Padhraic Smyth, Hal Stern, Gene Tsudik, Jessica Utts
14 Fellows of the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM): Pierre Baldi, Michael Carey, Rena Dechter, Paul Dourish, Nikil Dutt, David Eppstein, Michael Franz, Michael Goodrich, Ramesh Jain, Gary Olson, Judy Olson, Padhraic Smyth, Richard Taylor, Gene Tsudik
11 Fellows of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE): Pierre Baldi, Michael Carey, Nikil Dutt, Michael Franz, Michael Goodrich, Ramesh Jain, Crista Lopes, Sharad Mehrotra, Alexandru Nicolau, Marios Papaefthymiou, Gene Tsudik
7 Fellows of the American Statistical Association (ASA): Veronica Berrocal, Daniel Gillen, Wesley Johnson, Hernando Ombao, Babak Shahbaba, Hal Stern, Jessica Utts
2 members of Academia Europaea: Alex Nicolau  (2018) and Gene Tsudik
1 foreign member of the Royal Danish Academy of Sciences & Letters: Michael Goodrich (2018)
2 elected members of International Statistical Institute: Bin Nan, Annie Qu
1 member of the Board of Directors for the Computer Research Association (CRA): Gillian Hayes
2 Mercator Fellowships from the German Research Foundation: Alfred Kobsa, Stephan Mandt
ACM Charles P. "Chuck" Thacker Breakthrough in Computing Award: Michael Franz

Our alumni

Roy Fielding (B.S. '88, M.S. '93, Ph.D. '00) primary architect of HTTP/1.1
Paul Mockapetris (Ph.D. '82) inventor of the Domain Name System (DNS)
Larry Rowe (B.S. '70, PhD '76) professor emeritus, UC Berkeley
Barbara Kew (B.S. '75) CIO of Hill-Rom (medical technology)
Tim Kashani (B.S. '86) CEO of IT Mentors and Tony Award-winning

RESEARCH CENTERS

Cybersecurity Policy & Research Institute
Intel Science and Technology Center for Social Computing
Institute for Future Health
Institute for Genomics and Bioinformatics
Institute for Software Research
Institute for Virtual Environments and Computer Games
Center for Algorithms and Theory of Computation
Center for Emergency Response Technologies
Center for Machine Learning and Intelligent Systems
Laboratory for Ubiquitous Computing and Interaction 
Secure Computing and Networking Center

STUDENT ORGANIZATIONS

ACM (Association for Computing Machinery) - UC Irvine Chapter
Hack
ICS Student Council (ICSSC)
Management Information Student Society (MAISS)
Video Game Development Club (VGDC)
Women in Information and Computer Sciences (WICS)

CPRI is an NSA-Designated Center for Excellence in Cybersecurity in Research (CAE-R).





